Super Eagles forward Umar Sadiq has been  nominated for Player of the Month award The   striker continued his hot streak for UD Almeria in May and it proved enough to earn his side a promotion ticket to the La Liga Umar Sadiq scored two goals in four league games in May and did enough to help Almeria win the La Liga 2 title and earn an automatic promotion to the elite division.   Clergyman pledges support to grassroots soccer dev’t     Gauff set up French Open final against  Swiatek     ROAD TO DANKARO HOUSE: Peterside promises sweeping reforms…   His final day goal proved important for Almeria’s final hurdle and convinced the organizers of the league to nominate him alongside Jonathan Viera of UD Las Palmas and Real Valladolid’s Shon Weissman. It wasn’t the first time Sadiq will be nominated for Player of the Month award as he had previously won the award. He won the award for the month of February after scoring five goals and assisting two in the month. The attacker is currently a subject of transfer interests across Europe after scoring 18 goals and assisting nine in helping Almeria’s promotion push. With their status secured in La Liga, the club is seeking to hold on to the attacker as they face a potentially gruelling La Liga campaign.